<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Settings » User » Rights » User</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Use the search function and open the user that should be edited.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the  <strong>Authorisations</strong> section, activate the rights as listed in <a href="#table-editing-subscriptions-user-rights-back-end">Table 2</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
